Initial Recon
Started with an nmap scan against the target to confirm SMB was reachable.
bashnmap -p 445 -Pn 10.145.173.255
Output showed the host was actually a Domain Controller — Kerberos (88), LDAP (389), SMB (445), and Global Catalog (3268/3269) were all open. Important detail because it means we need to authenticate against a domain, not a workgroup.
