Key Takeaways

SMBDomain matters — when the target is a domain controller, the default . won't work. Set the actual domain or psexec will throw STATUS_LOGON_FAILURE even with valid credentials.
auxiliary/scanner/smb/smb_login is a useful diagnostic — it isolates whether the credentials work without involving exploit-stage complications.
search -f <filename> in Meterpreter does a full filesystem search; -d <path> narrows it down for speed.
PSExec via Metasploit authenticates over SMB and then uses ADMIN$ to drop a service executable that runs the payload — that's why the user needs admin rights and SMB needs to be reachable.
Kiwi (mimikatz) loaded via load kiwi opens up creds_all, lsa_dump_sam, and DCSync options for deeper credential extraction.


